Ha'Ayara Bo'Eret
comments: The song works in the style of Doom Metal, and was accompanied by a video clip consisting of videos taken in extermination camps. The song drew a large wave of protest at the time due to the fact that the band sang and played about the Holocaust using distortion and screams. The clip was broadcast on television and was followed by a protest article in the Haaretz newspaper. Knesset Speaker Dov Shilansky, himself a Holocaust survivor, who read the article, confronted live members of the band Zeev Tenenbaum and Amir Neubach as part of the "New Evening" program. The Knesset called for a ban on broadcasting the clip. The issue came up again for public discussion and again Dov Shilansky was invited to the evening's program, this time alongside MK Shevach Weiss, also a Holocaust survivor, who surprisingly praised the song and added that "the clip is excellent and the music makes you shiver." Two days later, the screening ban was lifted and the clip reappeared on the screens.
